  "notes": "Live Admin GraphQL 2026-04 evidence for metaobjectDefinitionUpdate immutability. The executable parity targets prove a standard definition enabled from Shopify's template catalog returns one IMMUTABLE userError and remains unchanged on immediate read-after-reject. The linked-product-options executable targets replay the captured local setup path through metaobjectDefinitionCreate, metaobjectCreate, metafieldDefinitionCreate, productCreate, productOptionsCreate, and then verify the captured IMMUTABLE display-name userError when updating the linked definition. The same live fixture records that this shop cannot create arbitrary non-standard `shopify--*` definitions (`NOT_AUTHORIZED`). Focused runtime tests cover deterministic local standard-template metadata, checked-in standard-template types without metadata, reserved `shopify--` namespace staging, linked product-option state, and the linked display-name guard. The local model does not yet represent Shopify's app-config-managed definition flag, so endpoint docs state that boundary rather than fabricating parity targets."
